President Joe Biden made a brief comment about his friend, Ellen Casey, at the Wilkes-Barre Scranton International Airport in Avoca, Pennsylvania. He described her as someone who loved fiercely and tenderly, attributing it to her Irish heritage. He compared her to Michelangelo, saying that she saw the best in people and brought out their potential. President Biden has known the Casey family for most of his life, as they lived near each other and attended the same parish. He praised Ellen Casey for raising a successful and decent family and credited Scranton for shaping his values. He mentioned that he couldn't attend her funeral due to security protocols and prior commitments. President Biden also declined to comment on his upcoming trip to Hawaii.